<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-06-13T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-06-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="833" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.61334/36: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-13T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                        1921—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. Department advised that Ecuadorean Congress will make no provision for
                            payment of Association’s debts beyond those of local <pb facs="1021" n="897" xml:id="pg_897"/> banks and <hi rend="italic">vale</hi><note n="34" xml:id="d833fn34">Vouchers or receipts, having the character
                                of promissory notes, for cacao delivered to the Association by the
                                growers.</note> holders regardless of promises made by the President
                            to special representative of Mercantile Bank of the Americas. You should
                            make discreet inquiry and inform Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>